🧠 Core Architecture

oc logs -f
   ↓
Node streaming layer
   ↓
Log processing + enrichment engine
   ↓
Sliding time window buffer
   ↓
UI state manager (filter/sort/view state)
   ↓
WebSocket
   ↓
React UI

---

⏳ SLIDING TIME WINDOW (DYNAMIC & REQUIRED)

- Logs are stored only for a time-based window
- Default: 30 minutes
- User can dynamically change window:

Supported values:

- 1 min
- 5 min
- 15 min
- 30 min
- 1 hour
- custom (user input)

Behavior:

- Logs outside window are automatically hidden
- Changing window updates UI instantly
- No fixed-size buffers allowed

---

🚨 CRITICAL UX RULE

SINGLE POD CONTEXT MODEL (MANDATORY)

The system MUST enforce:

- Only ONE pod is active at any time
- Switching pod must:
  - immediately clear UI
  - reset buffer
  - stop previous stream
  - start new stream

No multi-pod mixing allowed.

---

🧠 STREAM STABILITY & UX PROBLEM SOLUTIONS

❗ Problem: infinite streaming creates visual chaos

Solution: implement ALL of the following

---

🟢 1. Smart Auto-Scroll

- If user is at bottom → auto-scroll ON
- If user scrolls up → auto-scroll OFF
- Button: “Jump to live”

---

🟡 2. Pause on Scroll

- scrolling up pauses live view updates
- logs still collected in background buffer
- indicator:
  - LIVE
  - PAUSED
  - CATCHING UP

---

🔵 3. Batched Rendering System

- Do NOT render per log
- Batch updates every 100–200ms
- Append-only rendering

---

🟣 4. Time-Based Grouping (VERY IMPORTANT)

Group logs visually by time buckets:

- per second
- per 10 seconds
- per minute (configurable)

Example UI:

[12:01:00]
log line
log line

[12:01:10]
log line

---

🟠 5. Deduplication / Noise Reduction

If identical logs repeat:

- collapse into single entry:

(×124) timeout connecting to DB

- expandable to view instances

---

🔴 6. Log Burst Collapse

If many logs arrive in short time:

- collapse into “burst group”
- expandable section

